This paper deals with joint source-channel coding for transmitting a Gaussian source over a Gaussian broadcast channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves distortion analysis, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of multiple users in the broadcast channel suggests a possible connection to networking (cs.NI), and the discussion of outer bounds may involve complexity theory (cs.CC).
